description:
In relay/tests/socks5_helper.rs, the oneshot tx.send(()) (line 85) fires before the SOCKS5 success reply is written to the client (lines 93-96):

  // Signal that we received a CONNECT.
  let _ = tx.send(());

  // Connect to the real relay.
  let mut relay = TcpStream::connect(&target_addr).await...;

  // Success reply sent here — AFTER the signal
  client.write_all(&[0x05, 0x00, ...]).await.unwrap();

A test that awaits connect_received_rx and then immediately inspects connection state will see the signal before the CONNECT reply has been flushed. If there is any async scheduling jitter, the client's Socks5Stream::connect may not have received the success reply yet when the test assertion runs.

The signal should fire after write_all succeeds, not before the relay TCP connect.
